  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Warehouse Supervisor",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>Responsible for managing warehouses activities (fulfilment of orders, good receipts, inventory adjustment)</li><li>Monitor inbound and outbound shipments activities and maintain proper documentation</li><li>Responsible in managing and monitoring expiring products</li><li>Perform analysis on warehouse cost impact and stock movement</li><li>To manage warehouse storage cost and billing</li><li>Inbound container planning (on-time follow-up to prevent detention charges and updating container planning file)</li><li>Manage products mix and products turnover in respective managed warehouses</li><li>Planning for stock transfer between multiple warehouse locations</li><li>Lead projects to improve operational flow and cost reduction</li><li>Stock take/Cycle Count preparation and verification</li><li>Weekly inventory reconciliation and reporting of stock discrepancy</li><li>Prepare monthly reporting to the Operations Manager</li></ul><p><u><strong>Key Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>At least 5 years warehouse operation experience</li><li>Strong understanding in supply chain processes, preferably in Cold Supply Chain</li><li>Strong in analytical and data modelling skills and proficient in MS Excel, statistical analysis</li><li>Experience in Microsoft office (Excel, Word, Outlook etc.)</li><li>Experience with Navision, Infolog or other WMS systems is plus</li><li>Able to manage time efficiently and multi-task</li><li>Able to work under pressure</li><li>Excellent communication and facilitation skills with all associates and management levels</li><li>Good Interpersonal skills and pro-active, strong sense of ownership</li><li>Good problem-solving skills and demonstrated ability to think outside the box</li></ul>",
